			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> <date>19 July&#47;36</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My dear friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Some months past I was called upon<lb/> by the <persName>Revd. Mr A<add>&#63;</add></persName> who asked me if the 9c of the 2c of <persName>Job</persName><lb/> was correctly rendered &#8220;curse God and die&#8221; after examining<lb/> the Hebrew text I told him my impression was that<lb/> it should be &#8220;Bless God and die&#8221; how then he asked<lb/> are we to account for the words in the English Bible<lb/> I replied by the seventy translators regulating the points<lb/> which have caused them to <add>&#63;</add> gross <add>&#63;</add> upon<lb/> many texts.  That without the several points we could<lb/> not understand the true meaning of scripture&#44; and<lb/> that by means of the amounts we are made to<lb/> understand the subject matter&#44; I maintain<add>&#63;</add> my position<lb/> by the following examples.  The words in <persName>Job</persName> are<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> we read in 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Gens 22<add>&#63;</add> &#8220;and God blessed&#8221;<lb/> using the letters and points <add>Hebrew</add> and in the 145 psalm <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> &#8220;bless the Lord&#8221; and in other places <add>Hebrew</add> numbers 22<add>&#63;</add> <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> the letters &#38; points the same that is used in <persName>Job</persName> 2c. 9c. the word<lb/> to curse in the 22c. 6 of numbers is <add>Hebrew</add> and in <add>&#63;</add>.28c<lb/> 16 to 19<add>&#63;</add> to curse is <add>Hebrew</add> and the last word in the last verse<lb/> of the last chapter of <add>&#63;</add> to curse is <add>Hebrew</add> those were<lb/> all the authorities I could find applicable to the subject<lb/> having no one in this congregation in whose knowledge<lb/> I can confide.  I without hesitation apply to you at<lb/> your leisure forward me with your opinion discarding<lb/> all speculation as to the motives of <persName>Jobs</persName> wife&#8212;wishing<lb/> you all happiness&#44; I remain your friend</p>
				<p>Jacob Mordecai</p>
				<p>ask <persName>Mrs Hart</persName> if she succeeded<lb/> in getting <add>&#63;</add> work</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>To</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
